# Checkpoint layer rules

## Module ownership

- `store.py` — Durable crawl-progress persistence consumed by `orchestration/crawl_runner_bfs.py` to resume interrupted crawls.
- `cache.py` — General-purpose crawl-scoped cache primitives.
- `link_inventory_cache.py` — Cache for link-inventory rows built during the BFS crawl; consumed indirectly by `pipeline/` link-inventory streaming and `reporter/engine_io.py`.

## Resume-safety invariant

Checkpoint writes must be **idempotent and resumable**: a crash mid-write must never corrupt the state `crawl_runner_bfs.py` reads on resume. Prefer atomic write patterns (write-to-temp-then-replace) over in-place mutation of the checkpoint file.

## Testing

`link_inventory_cache.py` has a dedicated `tests/checkpoint/test_link_inventory_cache.py` testing its public functions in isolation (init, upsert, iteration, close), plus indirect coverage via `tests/pipeline/test_link_inventory_stream.py` and `tests/reporter/test_engine_io.py`.
